{"type":"message","id":"4eb7292a","parentId":"93b6c4ec","timestamp":"2026-05-20T10:06:35.162Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found and fixed a bug in `udd-web/lib/ai/service.ts` at line 357.\n\n**The bug:** `persistFiles` used `if (!result.files.length) return;` without checking if `result.files` is defined. If the AI generator ever returns a result with no `files` property (e.g., an error result or malformed response), this throws `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'length')`, crashing the task instead of failing gracefully.\n\n**The fix:** Changed to `if (!result.files?.length) return;` — optional chaining safely handles undefined `files` by returning early, which is the intended no-op behavior for empty file sets.\n\n**Why it matters:** This is in the critical path of every AI task completion. A single malformed generator response would leave the task hanging or unhandled instead of cleanly completing with no files."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":237,"output":180,"cacheRead":40704,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":41121,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1779271586488,"responseId":"msg_h6L6HT1dfv8QOJahmFyCS6A0"}}
